togam: the toga was the specific Roman garment, worn by none but Romans, the gens togata. It was a long, narrow shawl of unbleached wool, bluntly rounded to a point at each end. As the toga was only worn in civil life, its use here points, perhaps, to a completed conquest and organized government.
